S3 Connector Component

The S3 connector component allows your workflows
to interact with AWS s3 buckets and use them as
an object DB.


Usage : 

To use this component in a workflow configure your workflow.yaml


# Downloading a file

S3-Connector:
        - aws_secret_key: <your_secret_key>
        - aws_access_key: <your_access_key>
        - download:
                - bucket_name: <your_bucket_name>
                - file_name: <your_file_name>
                - file_path: <your_file_path>
                - output_path: <output_path>

# Uploading a file

S3-Connector:
        - aws_secret_key: <your_secret_key>
        - aws_access_key: <your_access_key>
        - upload:
                - bucket_name: <your_bucket_name>
                - file_name: <your_file_name>
                - file_path: <your_file_path>

# Listing files

S3-Connector:
        - aws_secret_key: <your_secret_key>
        - aws_access_key: <your_access_key>
        - list_files:
                - bucket_name: <your_bucket_name>


# Deleting Files

S3-Connector:
        - aws_secret_key: <your_secret_key>
        - aws_access_key: <your_access_key>
        - list_files:
                - bucket_name: <your_bucket_name>
                - file_name: <your_file_name>
                - file_version: <your_file_version>

